  "market_context": "NQ on the 1-hour chart after a prior bearish leg into the 21,440 area. Price made a shallow, slow retracement lower into the London session, suggesting a retracement rather than a true reversal lower, with the next session (New York) expected to drive direction.",
  "key_observation": "London session formed the session low and closed back over the down-close candles (change in state of delivery), then New York delivered a clean continuation higher with repeating expansion-retracement cycles rather than manipulating the previous day high.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified the shallow, slow move lower as a retracement signature rather than a reversal.",
    "Step 2: Watched for a low to form and looked for a protected swing via a closure over the down-close candles that built the low.",
    "Step 3: Confirmed the London session formed the session low with a candle closure back over those down-close candles, defining a London reversal.",
    "Step 4: Anticipated a New York continuation higher and marked the previous day high as the next draw on liquidity.",
    "Step 5: Checked whether price would manipulate that high (reversal signature) or expand directly through it (continuation signature) — observed continuation: large range into small range back into large range.",
    "Step 6: Tracked multiple expansion-retracement-expansion cycles confirming the continuation profile, until a messy small-range consolidation appeared after roughly two days of expansion."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "When London sweeps and closes back over down-close candles forming a protected swing, anticipate New York continuation in the opposite direction. Continuation looks like repeating large-range-into-small-range-into-large-range cycles, not a manipulation of the next draw on liquidity.",
